<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-19T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890g.01/220: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-19T14:00:00-05:00">October 19, 1929—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>277. Department’s No. 259, September 26, 11 a.m. Is there likely to be
                            delay in receiving the Iraqi communication regarding Article 28 of the
                            Public Education Law?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>